				</STIG_DATA>
				<STIG_DATA>
					<VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Rule_Title</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
					<ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Secure Boot must be enabled on Windows 11 systems.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
				</STIG_DATA>
				<STIG_DATA>
					<VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Vuln_Discuss</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
					<ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Secure Boot is a standard that ensures systems boot only to a trusted operating system. Secure Boot is required to support additional security features in Windows 11, including virtualization-based Security and Credential Guard. If Secure Boot is turned off, these security features will not function.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
				</STIG_DATA>
