				<STIG_DATA>
					<VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Vuln_Discuss</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
					<ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Kernel DMA Protection to protect PCs against drive-by Direct Memory Access (DMA) attacks using PCI hot plug devices connected to Thunderbolt 3 ports. Drive-by DMA attacks can lead to disclosure of sensitive information residing on a PC, or even injection of malware that allows attackers to bypass the lock screen or control PCs remotely.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
